pair of node pairs (a pair of contexts). Nevertheless, ï¬nding
the nearest neighbors by computing the distance between
all pairs of node pairs is extremely inefï¬cient and infeasible in application, which takes O(N 4) comparisons (as there are totally O(N 2) node pairs). Hence we implement Eq. (2)
using node-level embeddings. Speciï¬cally, considering that
we want to ï¬nd the nearest node pair based on both the raw
node features and structural features, we take the state-of-
the-art unsupervised graph representation learning method
MVGRL (Hassani & Khasahmadi, 2020) to learn the node embeddings XËœ âˆˆ RNÃ—FËœ from the observed graph (with validation and testing links masked off). We use XËœ to ï¬nd the nearest neighbors of node pairs. Therefore, âˆ€(vi, vj) âˆˆ V Ã— V, we deï¬ne its counterfactual link (va, vb) as

(va, vb) = arg min{d(xËœi, xËœa) + d(xËœj, xËœb) |

