where d(Â·, Â·) is speciï¬ed as the Euclidean distance on the embedding space of XËœ , and Î³ is a hyperparameter that deï¬nes the maximum distance that two nodes are considered as similar. When no node pair satisï¬es the above equation (i.e., there does not exist any node pair with opposite treatment that is close enough to the target node pair), we do not assign any nearest neighbor for the given node pair to ensure all the neighbors are similar enough (as substitutes) in the feature space. Thus, the counterfactual treatment matrix TCF and the counterfactual adjacency matrix ACF are deï¬ned as

